    {"children":[{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"房子西边"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (fángzi xībiān) - \"west side of the house\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"城市西边"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (chéngshì xībiān) - \"western part of the city\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"在西边"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (zài xībiān) - \"on the west side\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"西边的山"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (xībiān de shān) - \"the mountains to the west\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"往西边"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (wǎng xībiān) - \"toward the west side\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"}],"ordered":false,"spread":false,"start":null,"type":"list"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In Chinese culture and feng shui, the 西边 (west side) is associated with the setting sun and the\nend of the day. In traditional Chinese architecture, the west-facing areas often receive strong\nafternoon sun, making 西边 important for planning building orientation. The west is also\nsymbolically associated with autumn and maturity in Chinese five-element theory."}],"type":"paragraph"}
